ed rate quintiles per 100,000 population were the same as for CDC except for the last group, which was 7.07 to 15.27. The rate differences quintiles were −1.04 to −0.36, −0.35 to −0.06, −0.05 to 0.09, 0.10 to 0.2, and 0.29 to 2.50. Data were missing for Vermont.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":1110,"renderedHeight":162,"naturalWidth":null,"naturalHeight":null,"loading":null,"decoding":"async","altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 672 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":20905},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/pcd/issues/2020/images/20_0096_02-large.jpg?_=03659","alt":"Spatial distribution of unadjusted death rate per 100,000 population of deaths from gun violence across the contiguous United States, by state, in 2017 in 2 data sets: the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) Wide-ranging OnLine Data for Epidemiologic Research (WONDER) database (1) (panel 1a) and the Gun Violence Archive (GVA) (2) (panel 1b). Panel 1c shows the rate differences between the 2 data sets. Population data are from the US Census Bureau (3).","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":1110,"renderedHeight":108,"naturalWidth":null,"naturalHeight":null,"loading":null,"decoding":"async","altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 468 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":20905},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/5.0/img/logo/cdc-logo-tag-right.svg","alt":"Centers for Disease Control and Prevention","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":283,"renderedHeight":66,"naturalWidth":827,"naturalHeight":193,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":4780},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/contrib/libs/cdc/c2r/crlogo.svg","alt":"Content Credenti